\begin_inset Formula $c$
\end_inset

 is the speed of light and 
\begin_inset Formula $E$
\end_inset

 is the neutrino energy.
 Since 
\begin_inset Formula $mc^{2}\sim1\ \mathrm{eV}$
\end_inset

 and OPERA has 
\begin_inset Formula $E\sim17\ \mathrm{GeV}$
\end_inset

, the neutrinos are expected to go at a fraction 
\begin_inset Formula $\sim10^{-21}$
