 Also, the systematic uncertainty has asymmetric error bars.
 The notation 
\begin_inset Formula $x_{-\Delta x_{2}}^{+\Delta x_{1}}$
\end_inset

 means the true value of 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

 is likely between 
\begin_inset Formula $x-\Delta x_{2}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $x+\Delta x_{1}$
\end_inset

.
 When 
\begin_inset Formula $\Delta x_{1}=\Delta x_{2}$
\end_inset

 it is unnecessary to quote the two errors separately and you can use the
 more common notation for a symmetric error bar 
\begin_inset Formula $x\pm\Delta x$
\end_inset

.
 Also, note that they have pulled the common factor 
\begin_inset Formula $10^{-5}$
\end_inset

 out of the whole central value and error bar expression.
 This makes the result easier to read.
 The 
\begin_inset Formula $10^{-5}$
\end_inset

